title: Russian invasion of Ukraine and China's aggression over Taiwan threaten to create a world 'defined by danger', PM warns
description: Russia's war in Ukraine and China's aggression over Taiwan threaten to create a world "defined by danger, disorder and division", the UK prime minister has warned.

title: Fears two breakaway icebergs the size of Cornwall and London will impact marine wildlife
description: British scientists are tracking two of the world's biggest icebergs - one as big as Greater London and the other almost the size of Cornwall.

title: Costa Titch: The rapper who 'symbolised South Africa's rainbow nation aspirations'
description: South African rapper Costa Titch died after reportedly collapsing on stage during a festival performance.

title: RRR's Naatu Naatu makes history as first Indian song to win an Oscar
description: Naatu Naatu from Bollywood blockbuster RRR has made history as the first Indian song to win an Academy Award, taking the Oscar for best original music score.

title: Women in Berlin allowed to go topless in swimming pools
description: Women in Berlin will be allowed to go swimming topless after a discrimination complaint.

title: Pardons issued for 22,000 people arrested in Iran protests after Mahsa Amini's death
description: Some 22,000 people arrested in the recent Iran protests that swept the Islamic Republic have been pardoned, according to the country's head of judiciary.

title: Record-breaking floods in Australia as residents warned of crocodile-infested waters
description: A record-breaking flood has hit Australia's Queensland state with residents being told to limit their movements due to crocodile-infested waters.

title: Michelle Yeoh: From Miss Malaysia to first Asian winner of best actress Oscar
description: Michelle Yeoh has made history as the first Asian woman to win the Oscar for best actress for her performance in Everything Everywhere All At Once.

title: Russia-backed plot to cause unrest in Moldova has been foiled, police say
description: A Russia-backed plot to cause unrest in Moldova has been foiled, police in the country say.

title: Xi Jinping's ramping up of rhetoric is deliberate - and the drawing of battle lines is accelerating
description: Aside from the business at hand, events in China's Great Hall of the People really are an impressive spectacle.

title: China's military must become 'Great Wall of Steel', President Xi Jinping says
description: China must modernise its military to make it a "Great Wall of Steel", President Xi Jinping has said.
